Hello Mag!

### Set up your (currently my MacOS - Linux coming soon!) environment easily using ansible ###

1) Install homebrew
  1.1) Update your brew recipes: 'brew update'
  1.2) *OPTIONAL* Homebrew uses Github. Github has an API usage limit. Authenticated requests get a higher limit. 
  If you have a Github API Token, add it to the path for homebrew to use: 'export HOMEBREW_GITHUB_API_TOKEN="your_token"'

2) Install ansible 'brew install ansible'

3) Run ./bootstrap which will run the ansible-playbook 'ansible/setup-dotfiles.yaml', providing the environment variable 'dotfilespath'

4) The setup-dotfiles playbook will 
  4.1) Fetch your homebrew dependencies
  4.2) Symlink all you dotfiles to your home directory





### Adding additional dotfiles ###

1) Add the dotfile to the 'dotfiles' folder
2) Add the name of the dotfile to the 'ansible/tasks/linkdotfiles.yaml' playbook
